                    "img": "../static/images/chapter1/carbohydrates/carb_3.png",
                    "caption": "Barley"
                },
                {
                    "img": "../static/images/chapter1/carbohydrates/carb_4.png",
                    "caption": "Pumpkin"
                },
                {
                    "img": "../static/images/chapter1/carbohydrates/carb_5.png",
                    "caption": "Oat"
                }
            ],
            "advice": ["All of these should be cooked and served plain, without any added sugars, salts, or seasonings."]
        },
        "vitamins": {
            "subtitle": "Vitamins",
            "info": "Necessary for normal eye function (Vitamin A), bone development (Vitamin D), skin health (Vitamin E), and blood clotting (Vitamin K).",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "img": "../static/images/chapter1/vitamins/vitamin_1.png",
                    "caption": "Carrot"
                },
                {
                    "img": "../static/images/chapter1/vitamins/vitamin_2.png",
